text:
The ticket book of my youth! Ok, maybe that one is too old. I remember the ticket books having 1-2 E tickets (the awesome rides) and several of the other tickets (i.e., 3-5 C rides or whatever).

[Here is more info.](https://d23.com/e-ticket-memories-five-favorite-facts-about-ticket-books/)

Another edit: [Wiki also has info.](https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/E_ticket)

Edit to clarify: I remember the E tickets in the mid to late 70s when I was a kid.

It’s pretty close, IMO. Enjoy! 

Starbucks Heath Bars

1 cup packed brown sugar
1/2 cup (1 stick) butter, softened
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
1 egg
1 1/4 cup all-purpose flour
1/2 teaspoon baking soda
1/2 teaspoon salt
1/2 cup semi-sweet chocolate morsels
1/2 cup white chocolate chips
11 mini Heath bars

preheat oven to 375
 
grease 9-inch-square baking pan

beat sugar, butter and vanilla extract in large mixer bowl until creamy
 
beat in egg
 
combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl
 
gradually beat in to sugar
 
stir in morsels and chopped toffee
 
spread into prepared baking pan

bake 22 minutes
 
remove pan to wire rack; cool completely in pan on wire rack
 
refrigerate for 10 minutes or until chocolate is set
